<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
This genus clearly belongs in the galerucine section Diabroticites (
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="tribe" tribe="Luperini">Luperini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark, 2020" authorityName="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Prathapanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Diabroticina">Diabroticina</taxonomicName>
), as evidenced by the absence of basal spurs on the aedeagus, the absence of a rectangular lobe at the apex of the male abdomen, and the presence of bifid tarsal claws. However, the relationships within this section are debatable. The short setae along the lateral margin of the pronotum, as well as the longer setae on the elytral disc, suggest a relationship to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barber" authorityYear="1947" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acalymma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acalymma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Acalymma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Barber and 
<taxonomicName authority="BechynÃ©, 1956" authorityName="Bechyne" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Zischkaita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zischkaita" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Zischkaita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="BechynÃ©">Bechyne</normalizedToken>
. However, these genera have short genae. The large genae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark, 2020" authorityName="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Prathapanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prathapanius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Prathapanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest a relationship with 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise, 1922" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Isotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isotes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Isotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is reinforced by the fact that some (but not all) species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise, 1922" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Isotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isotes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Isotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a small keel on the aedeagus, although not nearly as large as the dorsal fin of 
<taxonomicName authority="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark, 2020" authorityName="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Prathapanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prathapanius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Prathapanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/1678-476620151054439452" author="Rodrigues, JMS" journalOrPublisher="Iheringia, Serie Zoologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" pagination="439 - 452" refId="B16" refString="Rodrigues, JMS, Mermudes, JRM, 2015. Comparative morphology of the type-species of Isotes and Synbrotica (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Galerucinae), with a new synonymy of species. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia 105 (4): 439 - 452, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/1678-476620151054439452" title="Comparative morphology of the type-species of Isotes and Synbrotica (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Galerucinae), with a new synonymy of species." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/1678-476620151054439452" volume="105" year="2015">Rodrigues and Mermudes 2015</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise, 1922" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Isotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isotes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Isotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the above-mentioned elytral setae. As already mentioned, the remarkable features of the male legs and genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark, 2020" authorityName="Viswajyothi &amp; Clark" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Prathapanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prathapanius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Prathapanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unlike any other known genus of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Galerucinae">Galerucinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
